Let 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1},\dots,X_{10}$
\end_inset

 be 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{Bernoulli}\left(p\right)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
The UMP level-
\begin_inset Formula $.0547$
\end_inset

 test for 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{0}:p=\frac{1}{2}$
\end_inset

 vs.
 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{1}:p=\frac{1}{4}$
\end_inset

 is the one that rejects for 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{f\left(\mathbf{x}|\frac{1}{4}\right)}{f\left(\mathbf{x}|\frac{1}{2}\right)}>k
\]

\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

.
 The power is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\beta\left(p\right)=P_{p}\left(\mathbf{x}\in RR\right)=P_{p}\left(\frac{f\left(\mathbf{x}|\frac{1}{4}\right)}{f\left(\mathbf{x}|\frac{1}{2}\right)}>k\right)
\]

\end_inset

The joint distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{i}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f\left(\mathbf{x}|p\right)=p^{\sum_{i=1}^{10}x_{i}}\left(1-p\right)^{10-\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_{i}}
\]

\end_inset

But 
\begin_inset Formula $T\left(\mathbf{X}\right)=\sum_{i=1}^{n}X_{i}$
\end_inset

 is a sufficient statistic for 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 is distributed 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{Binomial}\left(n,p\right)=\text{Binomial}\left(10,p\right)$
\end_inset

 and the test is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{g\left(t|\frac{1}{4}\right)}{g\left(t|\frac{1}{2}\right)}>k
\]

\end_inset

The ratio 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{g\left(t|\frac{1}{4}\right)}{g\left(t|\frac{1}{2}\right)}$
\end_inset

 is decreasing so for it to be greater than some 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 we need 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 to be smaller than some 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P_{p}\left(T<c\right)=.0547
\]

\end_inset

For 
\begin_inset Formula $c=2$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P_{p}\left(T\leq2|p=1/2\right)=.0546875
\]

\end_inset

And the value of the ratio 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{g\left(2|\frac{1}{4}\right)}{g\left(2|\frac{1}{2}\right)}=6.4072265
\]

\end_inset

So the test that rejects if 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{g\left(t|\frac{1}{4}\right)}{g\left(t|\frac{1}{2}\right)}>6.4072265
\]

\end_inset

is UMP level-
\begin_inset Formula $.0547$
\end_inset


