\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{X}$
\end_inset

 is sufficient for 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

, and distributed 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{n}\left(\theta,1/n\right)$
\end_inset

 and for 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{1}>\theta_{0}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\frac{g\left(t|\theta_{1}\right)}{g\left(t|\theta_{0}\right)} & =e^{-\frac{1}{2}\left(\left(t-\theta_{1}\right)^{2}-\left(t-\theta_{0}\right)^{2}\right)}\\
 & =e^{-\frac{1}{2}\left(\left(t-\theta_{1}\right)-\left(t-\theta_{0}\right)\right)\left(\left(t-\theta_{1}\right)+\left(t-\theta_{0}\right)\right)}\\
 & =e^{-\left(\theta_{0}-\theta_{1}\right)\left(2t-\left(\theta_{0}+\theta_{1}\right)\right)}\\
 & =e^{\left(\theta_{1}-\theta_{0}\right)\left(2t-\left(\theta_{0}+\theta_{1}\right)\right)}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

which is clearly an increasing function of 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

.
 So the test that rejects 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{0}$
\end_inset

 if 
