\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
The distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{X}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{n}\left(\theta,\sigma^{2}/n\right)$
\end_inset

.
 The size
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\alpha & =\sup_{\theta\in\Theta_{0}}P_{\theta}\left(\bar{X}>\theta_{0}+z_{\alpha}\frac{\sigma}{\sqrt{n}}\right)\\
 & =\sup_{\theta\in\Theta_{0}}P_{\theta}\left(\frac{\bar{X}-\theta}{\sigma/\sqrt{n}}>\frac{\theta_{0}-\theta}{\sigma/\sqrt{n}}+z_{\alpha}\right)\\
 & =\sup_{\theta\in\Theta_{0}}P_{\theta}\left(Z>\frac{\theta_{0}-\theta}{\sigma/\sqrt{n}}+z_{\alpha}\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset

This is clearly an increasing function of 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 since subtacting increasing the part of the support over which Z can be
 greater than.
 The largest probability occurs for smallest value of 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\theta_{0}-\theta}{\sigma/\sqrt{n}}$
\end_inset

 while 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta\leq\theta_{0}$
\end_inset

, which is 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\theta_{0}-\theta_{0}}{\sigma/\sqrt{n}}=0$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\alpha & =\sup_{\theta\in\Theta_{0}}P_{\theta}\left(Z>\frac{\theta_{0}-\theta_{0}}{\sigma/\sqrt{n}}+z_{\alpha}\right)\\
 & =\sup_{\theta\in\Theta_{0}}P_{\theta}\left(Z>z_{\alpha}\right)\\
 & =\alpha
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

